\begin{verbatim}
detrend(t, y, order = 1, bp = [])
\end{verbatim}
Detrend a signal \texttt{y} with respect to time \texttt{t} using a polynomial of order \texttt{order}.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{t}: Time vector


\item \texttt{y}: Signal to be detrended


\item \texttt{order}: Order of the polynomial (default is 1)


\item \texttt{bp}: Breakpoints for the polynomial (default is empty)

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{y\_detrended}: Detrended signal

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Notes}

\texttt{order} can be a vector if the trend is different over the segments defined by the breakpoints \texttt{bp}.

The breakpoints \texttt{bp} are the points where the polynomial order changes. If \texttt{bp} is empty, a single polynomial is fitted to the entire signal.

\begin{verbatim}
gradient(f::Vector{Real}, t; method = :cubic)
gradient(f::Matrix{Real}, t; method = :cubic, dims = 1)
\end{verbatim}
Compute the gradient of a function \texttt{f} at points \texttt{t}.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{f}: Function values


\item \texttt{t}: Points at which to evaluate the gradient


\item \texttt{method}: Interpolation method

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:linear}: Linear interpolation


\item \texttt{:cubic}: Cubic spline interpolation (default)

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{dims}: Dimension along which to compute the gradient

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{1}: Rows (default)


\item \texttt{2}: Columns

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{df}: Gradient of the vector \texttt{f} at points \texttt{t}

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note}

If \texttt{method} is \texttt{:cubic}, \texttt{t} must be an \texttt{AbstractRange}.

